The walnut carrot loaf was excellent, very moist and the icing was unbelievable, tasted so rich and like cream cheese icing. Went here for lunch, and was very disappointed. Ordered gluten free sandwich, and specifically requested gluten free bread because of a food allergy. The woman taking my order acted angry and rushed me through the line. When I got my sandwich, I noticed the bread looked like regular white bread. I asked if it was gluten free, and the woman who had taken my order got annoyed and took the sandwich back, and then gave me one with gluten free bread. All in all, I got very sick off this meal because they did not accommodate to my gluten free allergy like they claim they do. Instead of making me a new sandwich like I requested, they simply took off the bread and replaced it with gluten free, which I told them not to do. The service was terrible and extremely rude. They should not advertise gluten free if they are going to be annoyed with people who order it. I will not be going back!
